3.  **Performance Risks & Bottlenecks**
    There are virtually no sustained congestion risks. A single, very brief spike reached near capacity (9.35 Mbps) but was isolated and did not exceed the limit. The link consistently meets its service level agreements, operating in excellent condition over 99.9% of the time.

**Conclusion**
The current 10 Mbps link is substantially over-provisioned for existing and foreseeable future needs.
